      "description": "This 2002 BMW M3 (E46) is a superlative example of Bavarian engineering, featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine. The powerplant remains in peak operating condition, utilizing its six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear, high-revving power band. Mated to a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox, the drivetrain is paired with a factory-spec M Variable Differential Lock for exceptional corner-exit traction. This chassis has undergone proactive subframe reinforcement and shows no signs of fatigue or oxidation. The suspension kinematics are tight, and the throttle response is telepathic. This is a museum-quality specimen with flawless paint depth and a pristine interior, representing the zenith of naturally aspirated performance.",
